Rails Tempaltes:


In App > Layouts > Application.html.erb

you will find the html that is added to each and every page. 
only part that varies page to page is the content that i added in   <%= yield %> tag. 

So if we want to create headers and footers, we can add those is  App > Layouts > Application.html.erb adn it will be imported all over the app.


Create a route automatically: rails generate controller home index



